Entity Description: Built-in Mixpanel event triggered when an element is clicked

Property Description: Name of the event
The browser being used at the time the event was fired. (Not versioned)
The version number of the browser being used at the time the event was fired.
The city of the event sender, parsed from IP.
The X-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the browser's viewport when the event occurred.
The Y-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the browser's viewport when the event occurred.
The full URL of the webpage on which the event is triggered.

A default Mixpanel property to track the device as determined by Mixpanel's client-side SDKs. Events tracked from the same device and same user but different applications may not have the same $device_id. The reset method will change the device_id.
HTML classes of an element that the user has interacted with.
The name of the web host.
The referring URL at first arrival.
The referring domain at first arrival.
Version of the Mixpanel library used to enqueue or send this data.
Whether the current event was tracked by the Autocapture SDK feature.
ID of a screen recording that was being captured in the browser tab which tracked this event
The X-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the event target element.
The Y-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the event target element.
The operating system of the event sender.
The height of the entire page.
The width of the entire page.
The X-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the entire page.
The Y-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the entire page.
The region (state or province) of the event sender that is parsed from IP.
The X-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the screen.
The Y-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the screen.
The height of a device's screen.
The width of the screen of the device.
The specific HTML element that triggered the event (e.g., a button or link).
A default Mixpanel property to track the $identified_id passed into identify method client-side. Stored locally on the user's device using the register method.
The height of the browser's viewport at the time of the event.
The width of the browser's viewport at the time of the event.
The X-coordinate of the event, often synonymous with $pageX.
The Y-coordinate of the event, often synonymous with $pageY.
The country of the event sender, parsed from IP.
The name of the Mixpanel Library that sent the event.
Version of the Mixpanel library used to send this data over the network (not necessarily the same as the version which enqueued the data).
HTML href attribute of an element that the user has interacted with.
